text:
Kejadian yang saya alami th 1992 ketika masih SMA dengan apa yang saya lihat sekarang sangat berbeda.

Waktu th 1992 itu saya naik motor sendiri tanpa arah dan tujuan yang pasti. Hari Minggu siang dari Mojosongo Boyolali ke Pengging hanya sekedar"pit pitan". Dari Ngangkruk ke selatan, sampai pertigaan utara pasar lama belok kiri ketemu "tugu pipa", trus ke arah timur.
Beberapa ratus meter masuk kampung dan mentok ke sebuah pemakaman kuno dengan gapura ukiran batu serta terlihat dari luar banyak batu nisan (batu hitam). Depan makam kanan kiri jalan adalah rumah model Jawa yang halamannya menjadi satu dengan jalan tsb. Waktu itu suasana sepi tidak ada orang sama sekali. Dalam hati saya hanya bertanya, "apa ini makam Ki Ageng Kebo Kenongo".
Karena tidak ada orang dan jalan buntu maka saya putar arah kembali ke jalan raya Pengging, trus langsung pulang lewat arah selatan (Salakan - Sudimoro- Randusari).
Baru 35 tahun selanjutnya / beberapa waktu lalu saya di ajak teman ziarah makam Ki Ageng Kebo Kenongo. Saya sempat kaget karena apa yang sudah saya alami dan terlihat nyata oleh mata saya sendiri berbeda dengan kenyataan. Antara lain :
1. Secara fakta pintu masuk dari arah timur berbeda dengan pengalaman th 1992 bahwa pintu masuk dari arah barat.
2. Pengalaman th 1992 tsb kampung sebelah barat makam semua rumah model Jawa menghadap jalan dengan tanpa pagar dan semua terlihat bersih. Berbeda fakta bahwa bangunan dengan berbagai tipe.
3. Makam dikelilingi pagar dan gapura batu candi, fakta tidak demikian.
4. Secara fakta dari arah barat mentok pertigaan adalah tanah persawahan, sesuai penglihatan waktu itu adalah kompleks makam kuno.
Sampai saat ini saya belum menemukan jawaban atas kejadian yang pernah saya lihat atw alami tersebut, apakah th 1992 itu penglihatan saya di masukkan ke dimensi lain atau tidak. Yang jelas waktu itu saya dalam keadaan sehat jasmani dan rohani, cara berpikir juga sudah dewasa mengingat sudah kelas 2 SMA.
Saya masih ingat waktu itu saya berhenti di selatan jalan depan rumah yang menghadap utara dan depan kiri pintu masuk "Makam". Rumah dalam keadaan terbuka pintunya dan tidak terlihat para penghuni. Model rumah sebetulnya bisa dikatakan tidak kuno tapi lebih ke model rumah Jawa yang ada Dapa dan Gandok.
Logikanya bila saat ini ketika berhenti antara jalan dan halaman pasti akan terhalang pagar tapi waktu itu saya berhenti di selatan bahu jalan yang menyatu dengan halaman rumah tersebut.

Wallahualam...

Mungkin ada pemerhati spiritual atau pinisepuh Pengging bisa menjelaskan. Matur nuwun.🙏
textTranslated:
The incident that I experienced in 1992 when I was still in high school and what I see now are very different.

In 1992, I was riding my motorbike alone without a definite direction or destination. Sunday afternoon from Mojosongo Boyolali to Pengging is just a "pit pitan". From Ngangkruk, go south, until the T-junction north of the old market, turn left to meet the "pipe monument", then head east.
A few hundred meters into the village and you end up at an ancient cemetery with a stone carved gate and many tombstones (black stones) visible from the outside. In front of the tomb on either side of the road is a Javanese style house whose yard is one with the road. At that time it was quiet, there were no people at all. In my heart I just asked, "is this the grave of Ki Ageng Kebo Kenongo".
Because there were no people and the road was a dead end, I turned back to the Pengging highway, then went straight home via the south direction (Salakan - Sudimoro - Randusari).
Only 35 years later / some time ago I was invited by a friend to visit the grave of Ki Ageng Kebo Kenongo. I was shocked because what I had experienced and what was visible to my own eyes was different from reality. Among others :
1. In fact, the entrance from the east is different from the experience in 1992 that the entrance was from the west.
2. Experience in 1992 in the village to the west where all the Javanese style houses faced the road with no fences and everything looked clean. Differs in the fact that buildings are of various types.
3. The tomb is surrounded by a fence and a stone temple gate, this is not the case.
4. In fact, from the west, the T-junction is a rice field, according to the view at that time, it is an ancient tomb complex.
Until now I have not found an answer to the incident that I saw or experienced, whether in 1992 my vision was put into another dimension or not. What is clear at that time was that I was physically and mentally healthy, my way of thinking was also mature considering I was already in the 2nd year of high school.
I still remember that time I stopped south of the road in front of the house facing north and in front of the left entrance to the "Graveyard". The house had its doors open and the occupants could not be seen. The house model can actually be said to be not ancient but more like the Javanese house model of Dapa and Gandok.
Logically, now when you stop between the road and the yard it will definitely be blocked by a fence, but at that time I stopped on the south shoulder of the road that joins the yard of the house.

Wallahualam...

Maybe there are spiritual observers or Pengging elders who can explain. Thank you.🙏

textTranslated:
Aswaja Village

The tomb of Syech Jumadil Kubro. Together with upzisnu Kepil twigs

Syech Jumadil Kubro's grave is located on Jalan Arteri Yos Sudarso Number 1, Terboyo Kulon Village, Genuk District, Semarang City. His tomb complex is right on the side of the main road and is shaded by a large mosque. The mosque consists of 2 floors. The first floor contains the tomb of Syech Jumadil Kubro, while the second floor is used for pilgrim prayers. So, this is where the Upzisnu group carried out midday prayers in congregation.
The cupola of Syech Jumadil Kubro's tomb is lined with iron trails. The cupola is made of beautiful carved wood. The walls of the cupola are covered with white curtains.

name: Le 15
text:
Menurut sejarah yang dikenal masyarakat umum Mbah Mutamakkin memiliki nama asli Sumohadiwijaya beliau adalah seorang ningrat keturunan Raja dari pangeran benawa  . Ayahnya bernama sumohadinegoro atau pangeran benawa II. Ibunya putri raden tanu berasal dari persia keturunan sayyid ali bejagung.

Sejak kecil sumohadiwijaya sudah gemar membaca alqur'an, saat menginjak dewasa beliau merupakan seorang yang giat mencari ilmu, terutama ilmu agama islam, beliau pernah menimba ilmu kepada Syekh Muhammad Zayn al Mizjaji dari Yaman dan diberi gelar oleh gurunya "Al-Mutamakkin" yang artinya orang yang meneguhkan hati atau diyakini akan kesuciannya.

Selesai nyantri di yaman beliau tidak langsung pulang ke nusantara, beliau diajak gurunya menunaikan ibadah haji, saat beliau selesai melakukan ibadah haji ke Tanah Suci, beliau diantar pulang dan dibawa oleh murid syekh zayn dari bangsa jin. Ditengah perjalanan beliau di lempar di tengah samudera, lalu beliau meraih sebatang kayu yang ternyata seekorda ladang. Di tengah samudera beliau dibawa ikan tersebut, kemudian didaratkan pada sebuah pantai yang terletak di daerah Margoyoso Kabupaten Pati  Selanjutnya beliau bertempat tinggal di sebuah desa yang kemudian diberi nama Cebolek Kidul dan terakhir beliau bertempat tinggal di Desa Kajen.

Ada sebuah kejadian yang membuat beliau pergi ke Kajen Kabupaten Pati. Suatu ketika, saat akan melakukan shalat isya’, beliau melihat sebuah cahaya menjulang keatas dari arah barat, beliau ingin tahu apa yang terjadi. Lalu pergi esok harinya setelah ashar untuk membuktikan isyarat itu. Maka sampailah beliau pada sebuah gundukan tanah yang sekarang berada di sebelah barat Perguruan Islam Mathaliul Falah. Disitu beliau bertemu seorang lelaki yang sudah ber-haji bernama Haji Syamsuddin atau surya alam yang di yakini orang inilah sebagai empunya desa kajen . Konon, beliau adalah orang yang pertama kali melakukan ibadah haji di desa tersebut. Atas dasar itulah desa itu dinamakan Kajen (Jawa: kaji ijen). Satu-satunya orang yang sudah haji. Kemudian haji Syamsuddin menyerahkan desa Kajen kepada Mbah Mutamakkin. Tentunya, untuk mendakwahkan agama Islam di desa Kajen. Bahkan anak putrinya Nyai Qodimah diberikan kepada mbah Mutamakkin untuk dijadikan istri. Pada masanya, beliau adalah seorang alim yang punya karakteristik “aneh” atau Qawariqul Adah. Kenapa aneh? karena beliau, seorang ‘alim, memelihara dua ekor anjing. Kontan, kebanyakan ulama pada masa itu menganggap apa yang dilakukan Mbah Mutamakkin bertentangan dengan ajaran Islam. Kenapa sampai bisa beliau memelihara dua ekor anjing? Shahibul riwayat, menuturkan.

Beliau mendalami agama Islam dengan tekun dan sungguh- sungguh, disamping itu, beliau juga melakukan riyadhah. Riyadhah berarti melatih jiwa dari serangan hawa nafsu. Beliau lakukan dengan banyak cara. Diantaranya dengan mengurangi minum, makan dan tidur. Puncaknya, dalam rangka mengendalikan hawa nafsu, beliau melakukan puasa 40 hari dan malam. Pada hari ke-40 Mbah Mutamakkin meminta istrinya untuk menghidangkan makanan yang paling enak di hadapannya, dan meminta istrinya untuk mengikat tubuhnya pada tiang di rumah. Ada yang bilang : mengikat erat.

Setelah itu, Mbah Mutamakkin mengendalikan hawa nafsunya sekuat tenaga. Atas kehendak dan ijin Allah, beliau mampu mengendalikannya. Saat nafsu dan syahwatnya keluar, keduanya menjelma menjadi dua ekor anjing. (Ada yang bilang seekor anjing dan seekor singa.) Kedua ekor anjing tersebut ingin masuk kembali, tapi beliau tolak. Kemudian, kedua hewan tersebut dinamai Abdul Qahar dan Qamaruddin . Hal inilah yang kemudian menuai pertentangan. Karena dua ekor anjing dinamai dengan nama manusia.

Hal ini mengisyaratkan bahwa manusia yang tak bisa mengendalikan hawa nafsu, sama seperti anjing. Oleh sebab itu beliau pantas untuk dijadikan panutan hidup menuju ridlo Allah SWT
textTranslated:
According to history that is known to the general public, Mbah Mutamakkin has the original name of Sumohadiwijaya, he is a royal descendant of the King from the prince of Benawa. His father's name is Sumohadinegoro or Prince Benawa II. His mother, the daughter of Raden Tanu, comes from Persia, descended from Sayyid Ali Bejagung.

Sumohadiwijaya has been fond of reading the Qur'an since he was a child, when he grew up he was an active seeker of knowledge, especially Islamic knowledge, he once learned from Sheikh Muhammad Zayn al Mizjaji from Yemen and was given the title "Al-Mutamakkin" by his teacher which means a person who strengthens his heart or is convinced of his purity.

After completing his studies in Yemen, he did not immediately return to the archipelago, he was invited by his teacher to perform the Hajj, when he finished performing the Hajj to the Holy Land, he was escorted home and brought by a disciple of Sheikh Zayn from the jinn race. In the middle of the journey he was thrown in the middle of the ocean, then he grabbed a stick which turned out to be a field. In the middle of the ocean he brought the fish, then landed on a beach located in the Margoyoso district of Pati Regency. Further, he lived in a village that was later named Cebolek Kidul and finally he lived in Kajen Village.

There was an incident that made him go to Kajen Pati District. One time, when he was about to perform the Isha' prayer, he saw a light rising up from the west, he wanted to know what happened. Then go the next day after Asr to prove the signal. So he arrived at a mound of land that is now on the west side of the Mathaliul Falah Islamic School. There he met a man who had done Hajj named Haji Syamsuddin or Surya Alam who was believed to be the owner of Kajen village. It is said that he was the first person to perform Hajj in the village. On that basis the village was named Kajen (Javanese: kaji ijen). The only person who has done Hajj. Then Haji Syamsuddin handed over Kajen village to Mbah Mutamakkin. Of course, to preach Islam in Kajen village. Even his daughter Nyai Qodimah was given to mbah Mutamakkin to be his wife. At the time, he was a scholar who had "strange" characteristics or Qawariqul Adah. Why is it strange? because he, a scholar, kept two dogs. Kontan, most scholars at that time considered what Mbah Mutamakkin did against the teachings of Islam. Why can he keep two dogs? Shahibul narration, speaking.

He studied Islam diligently and earnestly, besides that, he also performed riyadah. Riyadhah means training the soul from the attacks of lust. He did it in many ways. Among them by reducing drinking, eating and sleeping. To top it off, in order to control his lust, he fasted for 40 days and nights. On the 40th day Mbah Mutamakkin asked his wife to serve the most delicious food in front of him, and asked his wife to tie his body to a pole at home. Some say: tie tightly.

After that, Mbah Mutamakkin controlled his lust as hard as he could. By God's will and permission, he is able to control it. When his lust and lust came out, they both turned into two dogs. (Some say a dog and a lion.) The two dogs wanted to go back in, but he refused. Later, the two animals were named Abdul Qahar and Qamaruddin. This is what then reaped the opposition. Because two dogs are named after people.

This indicates that humans who cannot control their passions are just like dogs. For this reason, he deserves to be used as a role model towards the ridlo of Allah SWT

name: Akhil Geztha Photography
text:
Kisah manusia yang mampu menaklukkan petir tercatat dalam legenda di Indonesia. Tokoh dalam kisah itu adalah Ki Ageng Selo, yang makamnya terletak di Desa Selo, Tawangharjo, Grobogan, Jawa Tengah. Lokasi makam berjarak sekitar 10 kilometer dari Kota Purwodadi.

Makam Ki Ageng Selo sekarang merupakan benda cagar budaya yang dilindungi UU Cagar Budaya No. 5 Tahun 1992 Jo. UU Cagar Budaya No. 11 Tahun 2010. Selain makam, termasuk juga masjid Ki Ageng Selo dan Tanah Magersari.

Jejak Ki Ageng Selo tercatat sejarah. Sosoknya disebut sebagai keturunan raja terakhir Majapahit, Brawijaya, dari garis Ki Getas Pandawa. Ki Ageng Selo juga diketahui sebagai guru pendiri Kesultanan Pajang, Sultan Adiwijaya.

Hidup sederhana sebagai petani, Ki Ageng Selo memperdalam ilmu filsafat dan agama sehingga memiliki pengaruh yang kuat dalam tatanan kehidupan masyarakat. Bahkan olah pikiran Ki Ageng Selo sangat didengarkan penduduk setempat.

Dikenal sebagai orang bijaksana dengan ilmu kanuragan yang tinggi, Ki Ageng Selo tak pernah tinggi hati. Ia menjadi pendengar yang baik dan mau membantu kesulitan yang dihadapi para petani.

Sebagai desa yang subur dan lumbung padi, suatu ketika keresahan petani muncul disebabkan lahan bertani menjadi lokasi sambaran petir. Akibatnya, hasil panen padi berkurang dan petani merasa was-was mengolah lahannya.

Suatu hari, saat sedang menggarap lahan sawahnya, cuaca mendung dan turun hujan. Lalu, petir menyambar Ki Ageng Selo. Dengan ilmu kanuragannya, Ki Ageng Selo menangkap petir yang berwujud naga, kemudian diikat pada pohon Gandrik di sekitar lahan sawahnya.

Ketika dibawa ke rumah, wujud naga itu disimpan dalam lemari yang kini bisa dilihat di area belakang pondok makam.

Hingga kini masyarakat Jawa percaya bila hujan turun dan muncul petir, mereka akan terhindar dari sambaran petir bila berucap “Gandrik anak putune Ki Ageng Selo (Gandrik anak cucunya Ki Ageng Selo)”.

Saat dibawa ke Sultan Demak, petir berupa naga berubah wujud menjadi seorang kakek, yang dikerangkeng dan ditempatkan di alun-alun.

Seorang nenek mendekati kerangkeng dan menyemburkan air dari kendi yang dibawanya ke arah si kakek. Petir menggelegar, wujud kakek dan nenek itu menghilang tiba-tiba.

Dalam satu foto yang dipajang di pendopo sebelah kanan selasar menuju makam, pengunjung bisa melihat gambar wujud naga dari petir yang ditangkap Ki Ageng Selo. Gambar tersebut dilukis oleh Ki Ageng Selo dengan judul “Lawang Bledeg” dan terpahat di pintu utama Masjid Agung Demak.

Letak makam Ki Ageng Selo berada di area belakang masjid. Sehingga, peziarah harus melewati jalan di samping masjid, menyusuri jalan selasar yang berujung pada pondok yang didominasi warna hijau. Dalam pondok itulah makam Ki Ageng Selo tersimpan.

Area selasar juga menjadi wilayah yang jangan lupa untuk dilihat peziarah, karena terdapat silsilah lengkap dari Ki Ageng Selo yang tersipan dalam pendopo.

Sebelum menyusuri selasar, pada dinding bangunan sebelah kanan jalan masuk selasar, peziarah bisa melihat tujuh pepali (larangan) Ki Ageng Selo, yang dinarasikan dalam sekar macapat, Dandanggula. Tertulis “Pepali-ku hargailah, (supaya) memberkahi, lagi pula selamat serta sehat”.

Larangan memetik tanaman yang ada dalam wilayah makam, juga harus dipatuhi peziarah. Terutama pohon Gandrik yang terdapat di sekitar pondok makam.

Selain itu, peziarah yang datang haruslah menjaga ketenangan, agar tidak mengganggu peziarah lain yang sedang melantunkan ayat-ayat doa dengan khusyuk.
textTranslated:
The story of a man who was able to conquer lightning is recorded in legend in Indonesia. The character in the story is Ki Ageng Selo, whose grave is located in Selo Village, Tawangharjo, Grobogan, Central Java. The location of the grave is about 10 kilometers from Purwodadi City.

Ki Ageng Selo's grave is now a cultural heritage object protected by the Cultural Heritage Law no. 5 of 1992 Jo. Cultural Heritage Law no. 11 of 2010. Apart from the tomb, it also includes the Ki Ageng Selo and Tanah Magersari mosques.

Ki Ageng Selo's footsteps are recorded in history. His figure is said to be a descendant of the last king of Majapahit, Brawijaya, from the line of Ki Getas Pandawa. Ki Ageng Selo is also known as the teacher of the founder of the Pajang Sultanate, Sultan Adiwijaya.

Living a simple life as a farmer, Ki Ageng Selo deepened his knowledge of philosophy and religion so that he had a strong influence on the fabric of people's lives. In fact, Ki Ageng Selo's thoughts were really listened to by local residents.

Known as a wise man with high knowledge of kanuragan, Ki Ageng Selo was never arrogant. He is a good listener and is willing to help with difficulties faced by farmers.

As a fertile village and rice barn, one day farmers' unrest arose because their farming land was the location of a lightning strike. As a result, rice yields are reduced and farmers feel anxious about cultivating their land.

One day, while he was working on his rice field, the weather was cloudy and it was raining. Then, lightning struck Ki Ageng Selo. With his kanuragan knowledge, Ki Ageng Selo caught lightning in the form of a dragon, then tied it to a Gandrik tree around his rice field.

When he was brought home, the dragon's form was kept in a cupboard which can now be seen in the area behind the tomb hut.

Until now, Javanese people believe that if it rains and lightning appears, they will avoid being struck by lightning if they say "Gandrik anak putune Ki Ageng Selo (Gandrik is the grandson of Ki Ageng Selo)".

When brought to the Sultan of Demak, the lightning in the form of a dragon transformed into an old man, who was caged and placed in the square.

A grandmother approached the cage and squirted water from the jug she was carrying towards the grandfather. Lightning boomed, and the grandfather and grandmother's forms suddenly disappeared.

In a photo displayed in the pavilion to the right of the hall leading to the tomb, visitors can see a picture of a dragon formed from lightning captured by Ki Ageng Selo. The picture was painted by Ki Ageng Selo with the title "Lawang Bledeg" and is carved on the main door of the Demak Grand Mosque.

The location of Ki Ageng Selo's grave is in the area behind the mosque. So, pilgrims have to pass through the road next to the mosque, along the corridor which ends at the hut which is dominated by green. In that hut is Ki Ageng Selo's grave.

The lobby area is also an area that pilgrims should not forget to see, because there is a complete genealogy of Ki Ageng Selo tucked away in the pavilion.

Before walking down the hall, on the wall of the building to the right of the entrance to the hall, pilgrims can see the seven pepali (prohibitions) of Ki Ageng Selo, which are narrated in the sekar macapat, Dandanggula. It says "My Pepali be appreciated, (so that) it will bless you, and be safe and healthy."

Pilgrims must also obey the prohibition on picking plants in the grave area. Especially the Gandrik trees found around the grave hut.

Apart from that, pilgrims who come must maintain calm, so as not to disturb other pilgrims who are chanting prayer verses fervently.

address: GWR2+927, Butuh, Gedongan, Plupuh, Dusun II, Gedongan, Kec. Plupuh, Kabupaten Sragen, Jawa Tengah 57283, Indonesia
name: moh ali rohman
text:
Saya datang kesana bersama rombongan hari Minggu. Tempat parkir ada dua tempat, satu di sebelah barat makam, satunya lagi di depan makam. Yang sebelah barat makam parkirannya lebih luas.

Sampai disana jam sebelas. Sebelum masuk, kita ambil air wudhu yang berada di pagar sebelah kanan gerbang masuk makam. Setelah itu kita bersama - sama masuk kemakam, didalam ada juru kunci yang mencatat para pengunjung yang datang.

Untuk yang datang secara rombongan, cukup pimpinan rombongan yang mendaftar ke juru kunci. Setelah mendaftar, kita di persilahkan masuk. Sampai di dalam juru kunci menjelaskan tentang siapa saja yang di makamkan bersama dalam satu cungkup (seperti rumah untuk makam orang yang dimuliakan) dengan Ki Ageng Butuh atau Joko Tingkir. Sebelum meninggalkan para peziarah, juru kunci memberi peringatan bahwa untuk hari minggu ziarah dibatasi maksimal lima belas menit.

Demikian review dari saya, semoga bermanfaat.
textTranslated:
I came there with a group on Sunday. There are two parking lots, one to the west of the grave, the other in front of the grave. To the west of the cemetery, the parking area is wider.

Get there at eleven. Before entering, we take ablution water which is on the fence to the right of the tomb entrance gate. After that we entered the tomb together, inside there was a caretaker who recorded the visitors who came.

For those who come as a group, just the group leader will register with the caretaker. After registering, we were invited to enter. Up until the caretaker explained who was buried together in one cupola (like a house for the grave of a glorified person) with Ki Ageng Need or Joko Tingkir. Before leaving the pilgrims, the caretaker warned them that on Sundays the pilgrimage was limited to a maximum of fifteen minutes.

That's my review, I hope it's useful.
title: Makam Joko Tingkir

address: GWR2+927, Butuh, Gedongan, Plupuh, Dusun II, Gedongan, Kec. Plupuh, Kabupaten Sragen, Jawa Tengah 57283, Indonesia
name: FA Ramdany
text:
Makam ini masih banyak yang belum tahu. Lokasinya yang berada di tengah-tengah pemukiman dan jauh dari perkotaan membuat makam ini tersembunyi.

Suasanya khas pedesaan masih kental kalau di sini. Apalagi, masih banyak rumah yang masih menggunakan gebyok, full kayu jati. Sehingga membuat suasananya semakin mantep seperti di film-film pendekar.

Lokasi yang berada tidak jauh dari sungai bengawan solo membuat nuansa paginya terasa eksotis. Jauh dari hingar bingar dengung deru mesin, kata bang Iwan. Ditambah kicaun perkutut yang seolah menantang untuk dibawa pulang.

Secara spiritual memang energinya masih banyak yang positif. Karena memang masih jarang yang berkunjung ke tempat ini. Sehingga cocok sekali untuk tempat bertafakkur dan mencari kedamaian.
textTranslated:
Many people still don't know about this tomb. Its location in the middle of a settlement and far from urban areas makes this tomb hidden.

The typical rural atmosphere is still strong here. Moreover, there are still many houses that still use gebyok, full of teak wood. This makes the atmosphere even more stable, like in warrior films.

The location not far from the Bengawan Solo River makes the morning feel exotic. "Far from the hustle and bustle of the roar of engines," said Bang Iwan. Plus the chirping of the turtle dove which seems challenging to take home.

Spiritually, there is still a lot of positive energy. Because it is still rare for people to visit this place. So it is very suitable for a place to pray and seek peace.
title: Makam Joko Tingkir

name: Nufahn
text:
Salah satu rekomendasi lokasi ziarah di daerah Klaten. Nama aslinya adalah Bagus Burhan. Ia adalah putra dari Mas Pajangswara (juga disebut Mas Ngabehi Ranggawarsita. Ayahnya adalah cucu dari Yasadipura II, pujangga utama Kasunanan Surakarta.

Ayah Bagus Burhan merupakan keturunan Kesultanan Pajang sedangkan ibunya adalah keturunan dari Kesultanan Demak. Bagus Burhan diasuh oleh Ki Tanujaya, abdi dari ayahnya.
textTranslated:
One of the recommended pilgrimage locations in the Klaten area. His real name is Bagus Burhan. He is the son of Mas Pajangswara (also called Mas Ngabehi Ranggawarsita. His father was the grandson of Yasadipura II, the main poet of Kasunanan Surakarta.

Bagus Burhan's father was a descendant of the Pajang Sultanate while his mother was a descendant of the Demak Sultanate. Bagus Burhan was raised by Ki Tanujaya, his father's servant.
title: Makam Ronggo Warsito

Saya turut bangga meskipun aslinya beliau dari Surakarta, dimakamkan disini karena disini tempat istrinya. Ronggo Warsito budayawan sastrawan yang unik bahkan hingga saat ini cara beliau menulis satire dan sinisme keadaan sosial politik kehidupan masyarakat sangat mengena, kreatif dan menghibur

Close to my village, here everything is neatly arranged, clean and solemn, all the people respect the graves of great writers of their time
I'm also proud, even though he was originally from Surakarta, he was buried here because this is where his wife lives. Ronggo Warsito is a unique cultural writer and even today the way he writes satire and cynicism about the social and political conditions of people's lives is very touching, creative and entertaining.

name: Azis abdul Rohman
text: Saridin atau sering disebut Syeh Jangkung adalah salah satu penyebar agama Islam di Indonesia yang terkenal di Karesidenan Pati. Selain terkenal di Pati, Jawa Tengah, Saridin atau Syech Jangkung ternyata juga diakui sebagai leluhur atau nenek moyang warga Dusun Dukuh yang terletak di Desa Glagah Kecamatan Glagah Kabupaten Banyuwangi, Jawa Timur. Serta di sejarah keturunan anak cucu syech jangkung yang pangreh praja antara tahun 1700 masehi s/d 1900 masehi di Karesidenan Pati menikah dengan trah Tubagus Panembahan Ratu I Sultan Zainul Arifin (cicit Sunan Gunung Jati) Kesultanan Cirebon, trah Mataram,trah pangeran Kudus(Sarengat), trah citrasoma,trah condronegara bupati pati dan diantara keturunan Syech Jangkung yaitu ada Dr.Moewardi adalah Pahlawan Nasional Kemerdekaan Indonesia yang gugur sebagai Pahlawan Kusuma bangsa yang masih keturunan langsung dari Syech Jangkung, Sunan Muria dan Sunan Kalijaga dari Raden Moekmin/Raden Tirtakusuma (Pangeran Tengah) putra syech jangkung dan Raden Ayu Pandanarum putri Kesultanan Cirebon Panembahan Ratu I Sultan Zainul Arifin garis silsilah ayah Dr.Moewardi Yaitu Mas Sastrowardojo/Raden Soemito Sastrowardojo. Raden Bagus Momok landoh(Sigit Gus Momok Landoh/Raden Saretno) putra Syech Jangkung dan Raden Ayu Retno Jinoli Putri Sultan Mataram ke 2 Sultan Anyakrawati Raden Mas djolang dan Ratu Tulung Ayu, garis silsilah Raden Bagus Momok landoh dari Syech Jangkung dan Raden Ayu Retno Jinoli. Syekh Jangkung dan Raden Ayu Retnodiluwih istri dari Kesultanan Palembang memiliki anak Dyah Sunti, dan dari istri gebanganom Semawis memiliki anak Raden Kulup (Pangeran Dagan), serta istri dari anak khatib tuban, dan istri bakirah anak Ki Prayoguna
textTranslated: Saridin or often called Syeh Jangkung is one of the well-known propagators of Islam in Indonesia in the Pati Residency. Apart from being famous in Pati, Central Java, Saridin or Syech Jangkung is also recognized as the ancestor or ancestor of the residents of Dukuh Hamlet which is located in Glagah Village, Glagah District, Banyuwangi Regency, East Java. And in the history of the descendants of the tall Syech's grandchildren who were pangreh praja between 1700 AD to 1900 AD in the Pati Residency were married to the Tubagus breed, Panembahan Ratu I Sultan Zainul Arifin (great-grandson of Sunan Gunung Jati), the Sultanate of Cirebon, the Mataram breed, the Kudus prince breed (Sarengat ), the citrasoma breed, the Condronegara breed of the regent of Pati and among the descendants of Syech Jangkung, namely Dr. Moewardi, who was the National Hero of Indonesian Independence who died as the Kusuma Hero of the nation who was a direct descendant of Syech Jangkung, Sunan Muria and Sunan Kalijaga from Raden Moekmin/Raden Tirtakusuma ( Tengah Prince) son of Syech Tinggi and Raden Ayu Pandanarum, daughter of the Cirebon Sultanate of Panembahan Ratu I Sultan Zainul Arifin, Dr. Moewardi's father's lineage, namely Mas Sastrowardojo/Raden Soemito Sastrowardojo. Raden Bagus Momok Landoh(Sigit Gus Momok Landoh/Raden Saretno) son of Syech Jangkung and Raden Ayu Retno Jinoli Daughter of the 2nd Sultan of Mataram Sultan Anyakrawati Raden Mas djolang and Ratu Tulung Ayu, lineage of Raden Bagus Momok landoh from Syech Jangkung and Raden Ayu Retno Jinoli . Syekh Jangkung and Raden Ayu Retnodiluwih, the wife of the Palembang Sultanate have a child, Dyah Sunti, and the wife of Gebanganom Semawis has a child, Raden Kulup (Prince Dagan), as well as the wife of the Khatib's son, Tuban, and the wife of Bakirah, the son of Ki Prayoguna.
title: MAKAM SYECH JANGKUNG (SARIDIN) WALIYUALLAH

text: Pertama kali berkunjung ke Makam Mbah Kubro, seperti berbeda banget dengan makan para wali... Makam para wali biasanya dilokasi yang tenang, jauh dari keramaian dan kadang lokasinya jauh masuk ke pelosok. Makam mbah Kubro berada dipinggir jalan pantura semarang jawa tengah. Lokasinya mudah di jangkau, berada disekitar jalan kaligawe. Makam tersebut unik karena masjidnya kecil dilantai dua dan makamnya berada dibawahnya... saat memasuki makam, suasananya khusyuk dan damai.. banyak peziarah harus bergantian masuk karena ruangan tidak terlalu besar. area parkir pun terbatas. namun karomah mbah Kubro sangat luar biasa sehingga menarik perhatian orang untuk mendapatkan barokah...
textTranslated: The first time I visited Mbah Kubro's grave, it seemed very different from eating for the saints... The graves of the saints are usually in quiet locations, far from the crowds and sometimes in remote locations. Mbah Kubro's grave is located on the side of the Pantura road, Semarang, Central Java. The location is easy to reach, around Jalan Kaligawe. The tomb is unique because the mosque is small on the second floor and the tomb is below it... when entering the tomb, the atmosphere is solemn and peaceful... many pilgrims have to take turns entering because the room is not too big. Parking area is also limited. But Mbah Kubro's karomah is so extraordinary that it attracts people's attention to get blessings...
title: Tomb of Waliyyulloh Syeikh Maulana Jumadil Kubro

name: Agung Budi K
text:
Pernah dengar cerita rakyat tentang seorang yang sakti mandraguna, yang sanggup menangkap petir. Ya beliaulah orang yang di legendakan mampu menangkap dan mengikat petir, siapa lagi kalau bukan Ki Ageng Sela.
Namanya juga legenda, cerita yang di lebih-lebihkan, barangkali saat itu Ki Ageng Sela yang hidup di abad ke 15 M sedang mengadakan eksperimen dengan tenaga listrik, cuma masyarakat di larang melihat dari dekat ya, karena tahu bahaya-nya listrik ini. Masuk akal nggak sih... masuk akal lah, kan ilmu kimia saja sudah berkembang di jaman Al-ghazali di Abad 10 M. Bisa jadi kan, Ki Ageng Sela ini sudah pernah belajar ke Timur Tengah, jadi memiliki ilmu yang di tanah jawa saat itu masih sesuatu yang aneh.
Portugis saja saat itu sudah menjajah kemana-mana, sambil membawa senjata meriam/kanon.
Buat menambah ilmu sejarah kerajaan-kerajaan Islam di Jawa, tidak ada salahnya bagi kalian yang seneng dengan ilmu sejarah mampir dan menggali sejarah lebih dalam di makan Ki Ageng Sela.
textTranslated:
Have you ever heard a folk tale about a powerful mandraguna, who was able to catch lightning? Yes, he is the person who is legendary for being able to catch and bind lightning, who else if not Ki Ageng Sela.
The name is also a legend, a story that is exaggerated, perhaps at that time Ki Ageng Sela, who lived in the 15th century AD, was conducting experiments with electric power, but people were prohibited from looking closely, because they knew the dangers of this electricity. Doesn't that make sense... it makes sense, the science of chemistry was already developed during the time of Al-Ghazali in the 10th century AD. It could be that Ki Ageng Sela had already studied in the Middle East, so he had the knowledge he had in Java at that time. it's still something strange.
At that time, the Portuguese had already colonized everywhere, carrying cannons.
To increase your knowledge of the history of Islamic kingdoms in Java, there's no harm in those of you who like historical knowledge to stop by and dig deeper into the history at Ki Ageng Sela.

text:

Di samping makam mbah selo ada jg makam bernisan kalimat tauhid, dan dikatakan saat menggali makam untuk warga setempat yang meninggal, banyak menemukan batu bata kuno seperti struktur pagar
textTranslated:
The grave of a village elder, with a headstone depicting the Majapahit sun flare. The location is not far from Troloyo's grave, it is very possible that he was an important Islamic figure in the Wilwatikta era.

Beside Mbah Selo's grave, there is also a tomb with an inscription on the phrase monotheism, and it is said that when digging graves for local residents who died, they found many ancient bricks like fence structures.

name: Setyo Widodo
text:
SYEKH Jumadil Kubra adalah salah satu sosok dalam penyebaran Islam di Tanah jawa. Sebagian besar pendapat menyakini, bahwa dia adalah bapak para wali di Nusantara dan Asia Tenggara.

Tapi masalahnya, belum ada satu bukti arkelogis yang cukup otentik untuk menyibak kabut identitas sosok yang bernama Syekh Jumadil Kubro, seperti makam atau prasasti. Alih-alih, makam dia bertebaran cukup banyak di pulau Jawa, bahkan sampai di Sulawesi.

Semua makammakam ini oleh penduduk setempat diyakini sebagai makam Syekh Jumadil Kubro, dan masih tetap diziarahi hingga hari ini. ”Kami juga tahu, ada beberapa tempat lain yang diyakini sebagai makam Syekh Jumadil Kubro. Tapi kami tetap yakin, di Semarang ini sebagai makam beliau.

Kami tetap menguri-uri keberadaan makam ini,”jelas Nur Ihsan. Memang tidak hanya di Semarang, situs yang berkaitan dengan Syekh Jumadil Kubro juga ditemukan di sebuah kompleks makam Islam kuno abad 14 di Trowulan, Mojokerto.

Di situ juga diyakini sebagai makam Syekh Jamaluddin Al Husain Al Akbar alias Sayyid Hussein Jumadil Kubro. Kompleks makam Islam kuno itu terletak di Desa Sentonorejo, Kecamatan Trowulan. Tepatnya sekitar 500 meter ke arah selatan dari Pendopo Agung Trowulan, serta sekitar 1 Km dari Museum Majapahit dan Kolam Segaran.
textTranslated:
SYEKH Jumadil Kubra is one of the figures in the spread of Islam in Java. Most opinions believe that he was the father of the saints in the archipelago and Southeast Asia.

But the problem is, there is not yet any archaeological evidence that is authentic enough to reveal the fog regarding the identity of the figure named Sheikh Jumadil Kubro, such as a tomb or an inscription. Instead, his graves are quite numerous on the island of Java, even in Sulawesi.

Local residents believe that all these tombs are the tombs of Sheikh Jumadil Kubro, and are still visited on pilgrimages to this day. "We also know that there are several other places that are believed to be the grave of Sheikh Jumadil Kubro. But we still believe that Semarang is his grave.

"We are still monitoring the existence of this tomb," explained Nur Ihsan. Indeed, not only in Semarang, sites related to Sheikh Jumadil Kubro were also found in an ancient Islamic tomb complex from the 14th century in Trowulan, Mojokerto.

It is also believed to be the grave of Sheikh Jamaluddin Al Husain Al Akbar alias Sayyid Hussein Jumadil Kubro. The ancient Islamic tomb complex is located in Sentonorejo Village, Trowulan District. To be precise, about 500 meters to the south from Pendopo Agung Trowulan, and about 1 km from the Majapahit Museum and Segaran Pool.
title: Tomb of Waliyyulloh Syeikh Maulana Jumadil Kubro

name: Dirty Harry
text:
Makan Ronggo Warsito di Palar Klaten. Raden Ngabehi Ronggo Warsito (1802–1873) adalah pujangga besar budaya Jawa yang hidup di Kasunanan Surakarta. Ia dianggap sebagai pujangga besar terakhir tanah Jawa.

Di tempat ini dimakamkan pula Carel Frederik Winter, Sr. (1799-1859) beliau adalah linguis Hindia-Belanda yang banyak bekerja sama dengan Ronggo Warsito dalam menulis berbagai kitab pertama yang menghubungkan kesusasteraan Jawa dan Barat.
C.F. Winter, begitu ia lebih dikenal, adalah seorang Indo yang ditugaskan untuk mendalami sastra Jawa oleh pemerintah kolonial. Pada gilirannya, ia bersahabat dengan Ronggo Warsito, pujangga dari Keraton Surakarta Hadiningrat. Hubungan keduanya kemudian bersifat mutualis. Karya abadinya adalah Kawi-Javaansch woordenboek (Kamus Kawi-Jawa).
textTranslated:
Eat Ronggo Warsito in Palar Klaten. Raden Ngabehi Ronggo Warsito (1802–1873) was a great poet of Javanese culture who lived in Kasunanan Surakarta. He is considered the last great poet of Java.

In this place, Carel Frederik Winter, Sr. is also buried. (1799-1859) he was a Dutch East Indies linguist who collaborated with Ronggo Warsito in writing various first books that connected Javanese and Western literature.
C.F. Winter, as he is better known, was an Indo who was assigned to study Javanese literature by the colonial government. In turn, he became friends with Ronggo Warsito, poet from the Surakarta Hadiningrat Palace. The relationship between the two then becomes mutualist. His immortal work is Kawi-Javaansch woordenboek (Kawi-Javanese Dictionary).
title: Makam Ronggo Warsito

Seperti layaknya makam jawa lainnya, Makam Joko Tingkir ini juga sering ramai didatangi oleh peziarah dari berbagai kota. Dan ketika Hari Raya Idul Fitri tiba, ada tradisi Larung Joko Tingkir yang diadakan oleh Pemerintah Kota Surakarta di Sungai Bengawan Solo. Dimulai dari Tempat Wisata Jurug sampai ke Desa Butuh Sragen.

And when Eid al-Fitr arrives, there is a Larung Joko Tingkir tradition held by the Surakarta City Government on the Bengawan Solo River. Starting from Jurug tourist attraction to the village of Need Sragen.
